product_name: Kiehl's Since 1851Super Multi-Corrective Eye Zone Treatment
summary: SummaryHighlightsClean IngredientsVeganSustainable PackagingGive BackThe Kiehl's Since 1851 Super Multi-Corrective Eye Zone Treatment is a cream that has niacinamide and collagen peptides that correct all four eye zones: brow bone area, eyelid, crow's feet & under-eye.
details: DetailsBenefitsThis anti-aging eye cream is clinically proven to visibly lift, smooth, de-puff and brighten the eye area to correct visible signs of aging around the brow bone, eyelid, crow's feet and under-eyeThis fast-absorbing, lightweight, non-greasy gel formula can be easily applied under makeupParaben-free, Dye/colorant-free, Fragrance-free, and Mineral oil-freeRenewable Niacinamide and Collagen PeptideOphthalmologist-tested and suitable for a sensitive & delicate eye areaKey IngredientsNiacinamide: a form of vitamin B-3 that helps visibly reduce fine lines and wrinkles while brightening the under-eye areaCollagen Peptide: comprised of three amino acids that help enhance skin's natural collagen while visibly improving crow's feet & firmness around the eye areaResearch ResultsIn a consumer study*:94% felt eyelid smoothed90% saw brow bone area lifted89% felt outer corner firmed (crow's feet)80% saw under-eye de-puffed100% Showed visible improvement in one or more of the following**:Lift & firmnessCrow's feet & wrinklesUnder-eye brightnessUneven & crepey texture*Based on an 8-week consumer study with 93 panelists**Average results based on expert grading in a 12-week clinical study with 96 panelists; photos are unretouched and show average results on lifted brow, above average results on crow's feet, crepey eyelidResults may vary. 100% based on percent of panelists showing improvement in one or more of the age signs listed based on expert grading in a 12-week clinical studyItem 2594299How To UseApply 2x a day, morning & night on clean, dry skin. Massage the lightweight, gel cream onto all four eye zones until formula absorbs into skin. For optimal results, try out the expert Eye Zone Workout massage techniques aimed to treat all four eye zones to visibly tighten, firm, & depuff for younger-looking eyes: Smooth the Eyelid: start from the inner corner and gently press the formula outward towards the temple. Lift the Brow Bone Area: gently press and hold, using an upward rolling motion to gently lift the brow. Firm Crow's Feet: gently massage, using an upward and outward motion, out to the temple. De-puff the Under-eye: tap lightly and rapidly from the inner corner to the outer corner.IngredientsAqua/Water, Dimethicone, Glycerin, Hydroxypropyl Tetrahydropyrantriol, Niacinamide, Alcohol Denat., Propylene Glycol, Silica, Propanediol, Polysilicone-11, Peg-10 Dimethicone, Di-C12-13 Alkyl Malate, Vaccinium Myrtillus Seed Oil, Dimethicone/Peg-10/15 Crosspolymer, Hydroxyethylpiperazine Ethane Sulfonic Acid, Bis-Peg/Ppg-16/16 Peg/Ppg-16/16 Dimethicone, Potassium Cetyl Phosphate, Carbomer, Ceteareth-20, Caffeine, Sodium Citrate, Sodium Hyaluronate, Sodium Hydroxide, Sodium Lactate, Palmitoyl Tetrapeptide-7, Palmitoyl Tripeptide-1, Adenosine, Ammonium Polyacryloyldimethyl Taurate, Boron Nitride, Dipropylene Glycol, Caprylic/Capric Triglyceride, Caprylyl Glycol, Trisodium Ethylenediamine Disuccinate, Polysorbate 20, Acrylates/C10-30 Alkyl Acrylate Crosspolymer, Butylene Glycol, Tocopherol, Pentaerythrityl Tetra-Di-T-Butyl Hydroxyhydrocinnamate, Chlorhexidine Digluconate, Chlorphenesin.Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details

reviews.headline: Amazing eye zone treatment!!!
reviews.comments: I received this as a free sample from Ulta for spending so much money online. I love this cream/gel or visa versa!! Its so hydrating!! It helps puffiness almost immediately. It does make my eyes water a little but its amazing otherwise!

reviews.headline: The smell...
reviews.comments: I like the consistency and it feels great on my skin but I just can't deal with the scent. Even after application, the scent doesn't go away.

reviews.headline: Best Eye Cream I've Ever Used
reviews.comments:
This eye cream is absolutely fabulous.  I'm in my early 50s & have horrible allergies.  The two things together mean I have a large set of luggage under my eyes.  I was hesitant to purchase this product where the price was a little high for such a small amount, but the majority of the previous reviews I read prompted me to give it a try.  It's mad an incredible difference in both the color & the puffiness of the bags under my eyes.  The circles are significantly lighter & nowhere near as puffy after using this product.  

The difference was noticed by my husband after only a week & a half.  He rarely notices any change in my appearance.   So for him to notice & speak up about says volumes.  My first container lasted over three months.  This is the second container I've purchased, & I fully anticipate being a lifelong customer of this product.

reviews.headline: Very weird smell!
reviews.comments: This product had such a strange overpowering smell that I couldn't even tell you if it was effective or not. I had to take it off because the strange smell was too strong for me.

reviews.headline: So far so good!
reviews.comments: I've only been using this product for a short time and I already see some improvement in depth of wrinkles and darkness around my eyes.

reviews.headline: Eh.
reviews.comments: Was hoping this worked better for the price. It does feel good and hydrating going on but hasn't done much for the bags under my eyes or pigmentation. Wouldn't recommend if you're looking to brighten the eyes.

reviews.headline: This is the most amazing eye cream I have ever tried!
reviews.comments: I use this eye cream daily. It feels very soothing immediately upon application. My eyes look years younger.

reviews.headline: Amazing product
reviews.comments: I love this eye cream. This product works immediately & it feels wonderful on my skin.

reviews.headline: love it
reviews.comments: I have been having weird texture issues especially under my eyes the last few years. this cleared that out within a week. even though it is expensive, this product is totally worth it.

reviews.headline: Makes my sensitive under eyes area puffy
reviews.comments: Like most under eye creams it makes my eyes puffy Because they're so sensitive underneath. I wanted to try something different I've been using Murad for the past few months and before that Lacome.  I'm raking this back and sticking with murad.

reviews.headline: Denatured Alcohol 7th ingredient!?
reviews.comments: Why is denatured alcohol the 7th ingredient? This is a known skin dehydrator & irritant. I checked after noticing tingling & having to use Aquaphor under the eye to protect moisture - I'm so open to someone explaining the reasoning for having this ingredient so high on the list - caffeine is a great ingredient but far down to make it worth while the dehydrating effects. Turn & Learn people! Eye creams are over priced moisturizers & rarely doing what they say they will.

faceoff_positive.comments: I received this in the mail to try. I made a tik tok about it because I love it so so much. I went to a plastic surgeon for a consultation for Botox under my eyes and he told me my under eye wrinkles are so bad because I have something called "jelly rolls". I really didn't want needles under my eyes so I was praying this kiehl's eye cream would pull through, and it did!! The fine lines are barely there and my concealer sits beautifully under my eyes. Thank you kiehls's!
faceoff_positive.headline: This problem has really helped my fine lines

faceoff_negative.comments: I love kiehls products. Sadly this was is a hard no for me. I started using it and then I would wake up the next morning with puffy undereyes, itchy ness and dry patches. I stopped using for a while to see if this was the cause, I used it again a couple weeks later and the same thing happened. and I'm not sensitive to skincare products at all. This wasn't cheap either. Very disappointing.
